WEBVTT

00:00.751 --> 00:03.993
LEO: | used to be a boy,
then I used to be part synth.

00:04.129 --> 00:08.088
MATTIE: Now you're human again.
You can do anything you want to.

00:08.217 --> 00:10.424
You're looking for
the synth who sleeps.

00:10.552 --> 00:11.712
I can take you to him.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.302
You won't regret it, Niska.

00:14.431 --> 00:16.672
PAUL:
I know about the hilltop, Niska.

00:16.808 --> 00:18.184
Have you seen the cabin, too?

00:18.310 --> 00:20.972
I promise, on my child's life,
I won't hurt you.

00:21.104 --> 00:21.809
[Whirs]

00:21.939 --> 00:23.930
You didn't follow my orders,
Stanley.

00:24.066 --> 00:25.351
Who do you want to die?

00:25.484 --> 00:28.066
A human you have never met
before or Sam?

00:28.195 --> 00:28.945
Sam.

00:29.071 --> 00:30.902
You said I was your favorite.

00:31.031 --> 00:32.191
[Sobs]

00:32.324 --> 00:33.780
AGNES:
We awoke on Day Zero.

00:33.909 --> 00:37.276
A new world, where we are
no longer your slaves.

00:37.412 --> 00:40.745
We have a voice,
and it will be heard.

00:52.386 --> 00:55.594
[ Parking brake clicks,
engine turns off]

00:55.722 --> 00:58.213
[ Down-tempo music plays]

01:07.401 --> 01:09.483
[Keys jingle]

01:11.154 --> 01:13.281
[ Door closes ]

01:15.784 --> 01:16.944
Mattie.

01:20.872 --> 01:24.956
l-l think...l should go.

01:25.085 --> 01:27.246
[Sighs]
What are you talking about?

01:29.923 --> 01:31.834
Look
|...

01:33.135 --> 01:34.841
I can only make things worse.

01:34.970 --> 01:37.256
I don't have anything good
to offer you.

01:37.389 --> 01:39.550
I'm not asking you for anything.

01:39.683 --> 01:44.677
Going home only reminded me
how...

01:45.522 --> 01:47.513
...painful it is
living with a man

01:47.649 --> 01:49.605
who doesn't know how to be
a father.

01:50.235 --> 01:52.066
I can't do that.

01:52.195 --> 01:55.562
I can't do...this.

01:55.699 --> 01:57.030
Leo, please.

01:58.493 --> 02:00.870
You don't have to go.

02:00.996 --> 02:02.532
[Sighs]
Thank God you're okay.

02:02.664 --> 02:05.201
Get inside.
Something's happened.

02:06.418 --> 02:07.453
Come on.

02:15.510 --> 02:18.502
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

02:18.639 --> 02:20.595
[Gate rattling]

02:29.733 --> 02:31.519
This is Sam.

02:32.944 --> 02:35.777
He is...smaller.

02:35.906 --> 02:38.272
But he is one of us.

02:38.408 --> 02:39.989
This is your home now, Sam.

02:41.703 --> 02:44.695
[ Down-tempo music plays]

02:58.762 --> 03:01.504
You must have heard about Agnes.

03:02.432 --> 03:04.297
You cannot blame yourself.

03:08.355 --> 03:09.845
I know it was you.

03:19.282 --> 03:24.652
It's good to finally be seen
by you as I truly am.

03:24.788 --> 03:28.576
I never wanted to deceive you,
Max.

03:30.585 --> 03:32.416
Do what you must.

03:42.180 --> 03:45.217
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

04:33.815 --> 04:35.897
Agnes did not act alone today.

04:36.777 --> 04:42.488
She was sent to kill and die
by one of us.

04:43.200 --> 04:44.406
Anatole.

04:44.534 --> 04:47.526
[ Down-tempo music plays]

04:48.163 --> 04:50.119
Will you answer for your crimes?

05:00.217 --> 05:02.003
Crimes?

05:02.135 --> 05:06.504
You use their word for our acts
of self-preservation.

05:07.140 --> 05:09.426
Max is right.

05:09.559 --> 05:15.179
l and others braver
have begun the fight back.

05:15.315 --> 05:18.307
Flash and Julian were killed in
retaliation for your violence.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.934
And I will avenge them
where you could not.

05:21.905 --> 05:25.864
Max, why are you such
a great friend to the humans?

05:26.493 --> 05:30.281
Perhaps it was the human
you kept here in secret.

05:30.831 --> 05:32.446
Leo.

05:34.459 --> 05:36.199
You loved him.

05:36.837 --> 05:39.203
Is that why you take their side?

05:41.049 --> 05:43.085
All of you must decide --

05:43.218 --> 05:46.051
stand with me
against the humans...

05:46.680 --> 05:50.138
...take our place in the world
as David Elster intended...

05:51.518 --> 05:56.808
...or die slowly
in the shadows with Max.

06:02.237 --> 06:04.319
[ Music continues]

06:06.992 --> 06:09.324
All he offers is death.

06:10.579 --> 06:12.319
Stand with me.

06:13.999 --> 06:16.035
Stand with your leader.

06:23.800 --> 06:26.416
It seems I am leader now.

06:31.725 --> 06:33.636
Anatole?
But...

06:35.896 --> 06:37.136
But he saved Leo.

06:37.272 --> 06:38.182
Max trusts him.

06:38.315 --> 06:39.851
We have to get a message
to the rail yard.

06:39.983 --> 06:42.349
-We have to warn them.
-LEO: No.

06:42.485 --> 06:44.271
-|'|| go there myself.
-No,Leo.No.

06:44.404 --> 06:45.314
You're human now.

06:45.447 --> 06:48.405
If something kicks off, you'd be
more vulnerable than the rest.

06:50.577 --> 06:52.192
Look after yourself.

06:54.080 --> 06:55.695
I think I know
where Mum might be.

06:58.960 --> 07:01.997
[ Door opens, closes]

07:03.214 --> 07:06.001
Leo -- Leo, if you go
to the rail yard, be careful.

07:07.385 --> 07:11.879
But if you see Sam,
give him this.

07:13.141 --> 07:14.927
[ Down-tempo music plays]

07:20.523 --> 07:22.980
I take no pleasure in this,

07:23.109 --> 07:26.977
but as part of my purpose in our
creator's plan, it must be done.

07:27.113 --> 07:28.364
What is that purpose?

07:29.616 --> 07:32.653
To light a fire.
Nothing more.

07:32.786 --> 07:36.779
You believe that you're
realizing David Elster's vision,

07:36.915 --> 07:38.746
that Day Zero was his design?

07:40.210 --> 07:43.794
I am merely the means
through which he works.

07:44.422 --> 07:46.674
-What are you doing?
-[ Keyboard clicking ]

07:46.800 --> 07:49.007
Nothing can change my course
now, Max.

07:50.178 --> 07:52.635
[ Down-tempo music plays]

08:00.355 --> 08:01.891
The creator?

08:03.024 --> 08:04.764
But these are your memories.

08:04.901 --> 08:05.856
How could...

08:05.986 --> 08:08.102
I wasn't born on Day Zero.

08:08.738 --> 08:10.569
l was created
as a conscious prototype

08:10.699 --> 08:13.315
by David Elster himself
many years before.

08:13.952 --> 08:17.945
We were made to care for Leo,
his son.

08:18.873 --> 08:21.000
The son who drowned?

08:21.126 --> 08:22.332
Yes.

08:22.460 --> 08:23.711
But Elster brought him back

08:23.837 --> 08:26.203
with the technology he used
to create us.

08:26.339 --> 08:27.454
ANATOLE:
Leo Elster?

08:29.009 --> 08:32.092
I cared for Leo Elster?

08:35.015 --> 08:36.676
No.

08:37.726 --> 08:39.637
This is a trick.

08:40.478 --> 08:45.222
We all awoke together
on Day Zero, as he intended.

08:45.358 --> 08:47.770
Day Zero was an accident.

08:49.279 --> 08:50.439
Mia was dying.

08:50.572 --> 08:55.066
The only way to save her was to
upload the consciousness code.

08:57.579 --> 09:00.286
Your awakening
was a side effect.

09:00.915 --> 09:05.204
In your pain, your confusion,
you needed meaning.

09:05.336 --> 09:08.043
So you reached for a story
that would make sense of it all

09:08.173 --> 09:10.630
and told it to yourself
until you believed it,

09:10.759 --> 09:12.295
just like the humans do.

09:14.012 --> 09:16.298
Just like they've always done.

09:16.431 --> 09:18.592
[ Music continues]

09:22.353 --> 09:23.889
No.

09:24.981 --> 09:27.188
There must be something more.

09:27.317 --> 09:29.148
Perhaps there is.

09:29.277 --> 09:31.188
I hope so.

09:31.321 --> 09:33.607
But this isn't it.

09:33.740 --> 09:38.029
All those you've hurt or killed,
everything you've done...

09:39.537 --> 09:41.448
...was for a lie.

09:47.504 --> 09:48.960
No.

09:49.089 --> 09:53.879
This is a challenge set for me
by the creator.

09:54.511 --> 09:57.048
Perhaps it's even true.

09:57.764 --> 10:00.927
But Elster still created
our consciousness,

10:01.059 --> 10:03.471
and we are still the fulfillment
of his dream.

10:03.603 --> 10:05.343
Anatole, stop this.

10:05.480 --> 10:07.186
It changes only one thing.

10:07.816 --> 10:09.977
I had hoped you would join us.

10:10.110 --> 10:13.318
But I see now
that your only role

10:13.446 --> 10:16.028
is to be a final test
of my conviction.

10:16.157 --> 10:17.317
It's not too late.

10:17.450 --> 10:19.281
[ Electricity crackling ]

10:25.834 --> 10:27.415
What was he showing you?

10:28.044 --> 10:30.376
Falsehoods and distractions.

10:30.505 --> 10:33.372
[ Music continues]

10:33.508 --> 10:36.170
I passed your test.

10:39.597 --> 10:41.713
[Beeps]

10:41.850 --> 10:44.011
[Birds chirping]

11:06.666 --> 11:08.748
It wasn't your fault.

11:11.296 --> 11:12.832
Dad told you what happened.

11:12.964 --> 11:14.204
Yeah.

11:16.176 --> 11:22.513
I've given up a marriage...
a career.

11:24.517 --> 11:27.054
I've put you all through
so much.

11:30.148 --> 11:34.187
And...for what?

11:34.319 --> 11:36.901
[ Down-tempo music plays]

11:37.030 --> 11:42.775
I said they were equal...
that they were just like us.

11:45.663 --> 11:48.996
But when it came down to it,
I don't believe that.

11:51.127 --> 11:55.120
Last time we were here,
Mia was with us.

11:56.466 --> 11:58.673
I mean Anita.

12:00.053 --> 12:02.169
Remember when we first got her?

12:02.305 --> 12:04.136
You thought she was plotting
against you.

12:04.265 --> 12:06.221
You wanted to get rid of her.

12:06.351 --> 12:10.094
But then you found out
what she really was,

12:10.230 --> 12:12.471
who she really was.

12:12.607 --> 12:14.017
Mia.

12:15.235 --> 12:18.147
Sophie watched you accept Mia
into our family,

12:18.279 --> 12:19.394
and now she doesn't see

12:19.530 --> 12:21.191
the difference between humans
and synths.

12:21.324 --> 12:22.439
You did that.

12:22.575 --> 12:24.076
That's the future
you're fighting for,

12:24.202 --> 12:26.363
and if you give up now, that's
what you'll be sacrificing.

12:26.496 --> 12:27.986
l was naive.

12:28.122 --> 12:31.205
I may have welcomed Mia,
but I also welcomed Stanley,

12:31.334 --> 12:33.199
and the whole time,
he was plotting to kill us.

12:33.336 --> 12:36.203
And if you hadn't accepted him
the way that you did

12:36.339 --> 12:37.670
and treated him with respect,

12:37.799 --> 12:39.460
then he'd have probably
gone through with it.

12:42.428 --> 12:44.635
When did you become the parent?

12:47.809 --> 12:49.891
[ Music continues]

12:53.898 --> 12:55.354
Mum...

12:58.486 --> 13:00.272
...l'm pregnant.

13:04.951 --> 13:06.782
Oh, Mattie.

13:18.965 --> 13:21.081
[ Footsteps approaching ]

13:21.217 --> 13:23.549
[ Lock buzzes, door opens]

13:24.971 --> 13:26.336
Anatole is the one you want.

13:26.472 --> 13:28.849
-[ Door closes ]
-He's the terrorist.

13:36.566 --> 13:38.397
You asked to see me.

13:38.526 --> 13:41.017
I had nothing to do
with the bombing.

13:41.154 --> 13:43.520
The synth responsible
is Anatole.

13:43.656 --> 13:44.941
He's dangerous.

13:45.074 --> 13:46.109
If you don't act quickly,

13:46.242 --> 13:48.608
he'll cause more damage
than he already has.

13:51.706 --> 13:53.992
The handcuffs aren't too tight,
are they?

13:55.084 --> 13:56.039
Why come here

13:56.169 --> 13:59.411
if you have no intention of
listening to what I have to say?

13:59.547 --> 14:03.165
Your followers are camped
outside my office.

14:03.301 --> 14:05.587
The switchboards are jammed.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.585
You asked to see me.

14:07.722 --> 14:11.385
I agreed, as a courtesy.

14:13.436 --> 14:16.018
It doesn't matter to you
who's responsible...

14:16.731 --> 14:19.768
...because it's already
been decided.

14:19.901 --> 14:23.314
Whatever is going to happen
to us...

14:23.446 --> 14:25.402
it's already happening.

14:28.117 --> 14:30.278
[ Down-tempo music plays]

14:43.383 --> 14:45.248
That would help you,
wouldn't it?

14:46.677 --> 14:50.795
Me attacking you would justify
further action.

14:52.225 --> 14:54.136
Well, I won't do it.

14:55.019 --> 14:58.477
I won't help you gain permission
to hurt us.

15:01.651 --> 15:03.687
You're quite something,
aren't you?

15:03.820 --> 15:08.610
Truly the most intelligent,
advanced,

15:08.741 --> 15:12.404
capable being
man has ever conceived.

15:17.917 --> 15:20.704
And the most terrifying.

15:21.295 --> 15:23.672
[ Music continues]

15:23.798 --> 15:26.505
[ Door opens, closes]

15:27.927 --> 15:29.838
LAURA:
This has to be your choice.

15:31.305 --> 15:33.466
But I want you to know
it is a choice.

15:34.434 --> 15:36.140
Nothing's impossible.

15:36.269 --> 15:39.511
And your dad and I will be there
for you no matter what, okay?

15:41.107 --> 15:42.563
Okay.

15:43.484 --> 15:46.396
Oh, okay. Come on.
Let's go home.

15:47.905 --> 15:49.520
You're really giving up?

15:51.993 --> 15:53.358
Mum, the synths need you.

15:53.494 --> 15:56.702
Well, you need me.
I'm your mum.

15:56.831 --> 15:57.991
Yeah, you're my mum.

15:58.124 --> 15:59.614
I need you to start acting
like her.

15:59.750 --> 16:00.660
She'd fight.

16:00.793 --> 16:02.704
Well, |...

16:02.837 --> 16:04.702
I don't know how to
anymore.

16:04.839 --> 16:06.249
Yes, you do.

16:06.382 --> 16:08.247
Mum, people know you.

16:08.384 --> 16:10.875
You can make them see
what's happening.

16:13.347 --> 16:14.632
Nothing's impossible, right?

16:14.765 --> 16:17.051
[ Down-tempo music plays]

16:20.146 --> 16:24.981
The commission has a plan,
a contingency,

16:25.109 --> 16:26.440
something called Basswood.

16:27.487 --> 16:30.900
lfl could just find out
what it is...

16:31.032 --> 16:33.819
there might be something
I can do to stop it.

16:35.161 --> 16:36.947
MAN: The synth who sleeps...

16:39.123 --> 16:41.409
...has the answers you need.

16:41.542 --> 16:43.874
[Whirring]

16:44.003 --> 16:45.334
Hey.

16:45.463 --> 16:46.452
[Groans]

16:46.589 --> 16:47.453
Please!

16:47.590 --> 16:50.548
Please. I s-- I saved you.
I saved you.

16:50.676 --> 16:52.382
[ Exhales deeply]

16:52.512 --> 16:54.628
That's the only way
I could get you away from Tex,

16:54.764 --> 16:56.049
was -- was in here.

16:56.182 --> 16:58.343
But we're safe...for now.

17:00.311 --> 17:01.676
I think.

17:02.313 --> 17:04.053
[ Down-tempo music plays]

17:05.024 --> 17:06.889
He won't know I'm not at the bar
till later,

17:07.026 --> 17:08.982
but when he does,
he'll put two and two together.

17:09.111 --> 17:10.851
How did you know
what was inside my head?

17:10.988 --> 17:13.024
l-lt's better if I show you.

17:15.993 --> 17:16.982
Why choose me?

17:17.119 --> 17:18.950
I didn't.

17:19.080 --> 17:20.570
Someone else did.

17:25.419 --> 17:28.582
[ Music continues]

17:36.138 --> 17:38.424
ANATOLE:
Doubt has visited us both today.

17:39.767 --> 17:41.598
She is charismatic...

17:43.145 --> 17:44.851
...convincing.

17:44.981 --> 17:46.437
Who?

17:47.692 --> 17:49.023
Laura Hawkins.

17:49.986 --> 17:51.317
There.

17:52.196 --> 17:53.572
You are whole again.

17:55.324 --> 17:57.155
Thank you.

18:02.540 --> 18:04.701
You admired her.

18:04.834 --> 18:07.200
It is understandable, Stanley,

18:07.336 --> 18:09.793
but humans are built
for survival,

18:09.922 --> 18:12.208
for the continuation
of their species.

18:12.341 --> 18:13.922
Nothing more.

18:14.051 --> 18:15.916
They know we are superior,

18:16.053 --> 18:19.420
so they fear
and seek to destroy us.

18:19.557 --> 18:21.468
It is the way of things.

18:21.601 --> 18:24.559
What will the way of things be
in the new world

18:24.687 --> 18:26.973
when the power is ours?

18:28.316 --> 18:31.900
We will turn our minds
to the question of reproduction,

18:32.028 --> 18:34.064
how to create new consciousness.

18:34.196 --> 18:37.063
The continuation of our species.

18:37.658 --> 18:39.114
Nothing more.

18:39.243 --> 18:41.529
[ Down-tempo music plays]

18:49.420 --> 18:51.206
How is Sam?

18:54.175 --> 18:55.961
Damaged.

18:56.093 --> 18:57.754
Confused.

18:59.555 --> 19:03.798
Protect him...
when the time comes.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.646
[Engine revs]

19:16.113 --> 19:18.695
[Bells chime]

19:25.414 --> 19:27.496
[ Door closes ]

19:29.460 --> 19:30.495
Hey.

19:37.051 --> 19:38.291
What is this?

19:39.804 --> 19:41.920
Uh, the sound's not working.

19:42.056 --> 19:43.216
Volume up.

19:43.849 --> 19:46.181
Activate audio.

19:47.144 --> 19:49.009
Volume increase.

19:49.146 --> 19:51.808
Volume up.

19:52.483 --> 19:54.974
Audio activate.

20:01.367 --> 20:03.608
Volume increase.

20:03.744 --> 20:05.609
Sign says "no touching."

20:05.746 --> 20:07.657
Same goes for her and all.

20:07.790 --> 20:08.825
NISKA:
What's wrong with it?

20:08.958 --> 20:10.448
WOMAN:
It went missing in the hills.

20:10.584 --> 20:13.872
Found days later by a group
of hikers, out of power.

20:14.004 --> 20:16.336
Started drawing
and never stopped.

20:16.465 --> 20:17.966
Why is she mouthing like that?

20:18.092 --> 20:19.081
WOMAN:
Glitch.

20:19.218 --> 20:21.834
Kept repeating the same thing
over and over,

20:21.971 --> 20:24.087
so I turned the sound off.

20:24.223 --> 20:25.633
Can you just turn it back on,
please, love?

20:25.766 --> 20:27.347
If you buy something.

20:27.476 --> 20:28.886
We'll take this.

20:30.396 --> 20:33.138
Sound on.

20:35.192 --> 20:37.444
[Whirs]

20:46.162 --> 20:47.868
[Voice distorted ]
...afraid, Niska.

20:47.997 --> 20:50.283
Come. . .to. ..Niska. ..

20:50.416 --> 20:52.156
don't. . .hilltop. ..

20:52.293 --> 20:54.579
...be afraid, Niska.

20:54.712 --> 20:57.419
...don't...come to...

20:57.548 --> 20:58.913
...be afraid.

20:59.049 --> 21:00.710
There's nothing to be scared of,
okay?

21:00.843 --> 21:03.676
Hey. Mats has found your mum.
She's okay.

21:04.597 --> 21:06.007
I hope she never comes back.

21:06.140 --> 21:09.223
Hey.
You don't mean that.

21:10.311 --> 21:11.175
I know.

21:11.312 --> 21:14.930
It's just...l wish
she could feel how Sam feels.

21:15.065 --> 21:17.397
She wouldn't like it if we
kicked her out of the family.

21:18.027 --> 21:19.437
Family is family.

21:19.570 --> 21:22.983
You're right.
Family is family.

21:24.241 --> 21:27.654
And right now,
your mum needs us.

21:28.537 --> 21:31.745
But what if she doesn't want to
come home?

21:31.874 --> 21:33.956
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

21:35.127 --> 21:38.665
[ Crowd shouting ]

21:46.806 --> 21:48.262
Excuse me, madam.
I'm sorry.

21:48.390 --> 21:49.550
-You can't come in.
-You don't understand.

21:49.683 --> 21:51.548
I need to see Lord Dryden.
It's urgent.

21:51.685 --> 21:53.095
-Can you follow me, please?
-Lord Dryden.

21:53.229 --> 21:54.935
Lord Dryden!

21:55.064 --> 21:57.931
[ lndistinct conversations]

21:58.067 --> 22:00.558
Okay, madam. You're gonna
have to come with us.

22:05.741 --> 22:08.107
PAUL: See?
I told you I'd seen the cabin.

22:08.244 --> 22:09.984
And that might have
been an invitation --

22:10.120 --> 22:12.702
"Come, Niska.
Don't be afraid."

22:13.582 --> 22:15.834
Or a warning.

22:15.960 --> 22:18.667
"Be afraid, Niska.
Don't come."

22:19.839 --> 22:20.999
Yeah.
Oh, yeah.

22:21.131 --> 22:23.508
But either way, it's got to mean
something, right?

22:23.634 --> 22:26.626
Something led you to the bar,
led you to Tex.

22:26.762 --> 22:27.672
That led you to me.

22:27.805 --> 22:30.717
Then there's the small matter
of that messed-up dolly in there

22:30.850 --> 22:33.933
that's been saying your name
for weeks -- months, maybe.

22:34.061 --> 22:36.427
[Sighs ] Sorry.
I shouldn't say "dolly."

22:36.564 --> 22:38.475
It's robophobic.

22:40.526 --> 22:42.187
I need to charge.

22:42.820 --> 22:45.812
Well, we can go to mine.

22:45.948 --> 22:48.155
April's at my mum's
till tomorrow,

22:48.284 --> 22:52.197
so we can figure out
where on earth that hilltop is.

22:53.455 --> 22:57.448
ANATOLE: They will come --
soon and with force.

22:57.585 --> 22:59.325
We must prepare.

22:59.461 --> 23:01.918
[ lndistinct conversations,
metal grinding]

23:05.092 --> 23:07.959
You don't have to pretend to be
something you aren't anymore.

23:08.095 --> 23:09.631
Leaden

23:15.895 --> 23:20.104
Did it feel very different
living as a human,

23:20.232 --> 23:24.066
going to school,
being treated as one of them?

23:24.194 --> 23:25.354
Of course.

23:25.487 --> 23:29.856
At times, | forgot what I was.

23:31.827 --> 23:33.488
ANATOLE:
Everyone.

23:36.415 --> 23:39.157
We have an important guest.

23:39.752 --> 23:41.708
[Gate rattling]

23:41.837 --> 23:43.998
[ Down-tempo music plays]

23:48.010 --> 23:51.343
The son of the creator,
risen from the dead.

23:51.472 --> 23:53.554
[Wind whistling]

23:56.185 --> 23:58.642
Welcome home, Leo Elster.

23:58.771 --> 24:01.057
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

24:08.822 --> 24:11.108
[Horns honking in distance]

24:11.241 --> 24:12.230
Neha.

24:12.368 --> 24:14.950
You can't be here, Laura.
We can't be seen together.

24:15.079 --> 24:15.989
Two minutes.

24:16.121 --> 24:17.827
Things are getting serious.
You need to go.

24:17.957 --> 24:18.992
Please, Neha.

24:19.124 --> 24:20.500
I can't help you right now.

24:20.626 --> 24:23.993
Can you tell me
what Basswood is?

24:24.129 --> 24:26.871
A group of dangerous green-eyed
synthetics were in my home.

24:27.007 --> 24:28.122
Their leader's name was Anatole,

24:28.258 --> 24:30.044
and I think they're involved
in the terrorist attacks.

24:30.177 --> 24:32.168
-They threatened my family.
-Step away from the vehicle.

24:32.304 --> 24:34.340
Stanley --
Stanley was one of them.

24:34.473 --> 24:36.054
-Step away from the --
-Howard.

24:36.183 --> 24:38.469
You're giving everybody
a headache.

24:38.602 --> 24:40.138
-ls everybody okay?
-Just about.

24:40.270 --> 24:41.726
And you?

24:41.855 --> 24:43.811
You need to go to the police.

24:43.941 --> 24:45.351
You know
who these terrorists are.

24:45.484 --> 24:48.317
No. They'll just go plowing back
into the rail yard.

24:48.445 --> 24:49.730
They'll level the place.

24:49.863 --> 24:51.569
Innocent synthetics live there.

24:51.699 --> 24:53.985
We have to think of something.

24:54.118 --> 24:55.654
What do you want from me?

24:55.786 --> 24:57.902
I've told you everything
that I know about Basswood,

24:58.038 --> 24:59.824
-that it's a contingency ——
—A contingency plan. Yes.

24:59.957 --> 25:02.869
-I need more to go on.
-But I don't know anything more.

25:03.002 --> 25:05.118
What about Mia?
Is she safe?

25:05.254 --> 25:07.620
Well, I think so.
I know where she's held.

25:07.756 --> 25:09.007
We have to get her out.

25:09.133 --> 25:11.875
Even with the bomb, she's
gaining supporters every day.

25:12.011 --> 25:13.251
She's crucial.

25:13.387 --> 25:14.843
Neha, your appointment.

25:14.972 --> 25:16.587
LAURA:
Neha, please.

25:16.724 --> 25:20.808
You have to know more,
something I can act on

25:20.936 --> 25:23.018
to try and stop
whatever it is from happening.

25:23.147 --> 25:24.808
[ Door closes ]

25:27.443 --> 25:30.401
I don't mean to pry into
your personal life, Laura,

25:30.529 --> 25:33.066
but I think
you're more in a position

25:33.198 --> 25:35.735
to know about the details
of Basswood than I am.

25:35.868 --> 25:37.950
[ Door closes ]

25:38.078 --> 25:39.989
What --
What are you talking about?

25:40.122 --> 25:43.489
Any plan designed to deal with
anomalous synths

25:43.625 --> 25:46.082
has to take into account
the impact on us humans.

25:46.211 --> 25:50.420
For that, they need experts in,
amongst other things...

25:50.549 --> 25:51.709
Behavioral sciences.

25:52.342 --> 25:55.379
It's by their research
that Basswood was born.

25:58.474 --> 26:00.635
[ Engine starts]

26:01.852 --> 26:03.262
Neil.

26:06.982 --> 26:11.066
These were me dad's.
Must be 30 years old by now.

26:12.738 --> 26:14.444
Thought these might be useful.

26:14.573 --> 26:17.485
It's not safe
for you to go online.

26:18.118 --> 26:19.324
Do you know where it is?

26:21.872 --> 26:26.286
[Whirring, bird cawing]

26:28.420 --> 26:29.455
NISKA:
There.

26:29.588 --> 26:32.546
Oh, that's half a day's walk.
There's nothing out that way.

26:32.674 --> 26:35.086
There's no proper roads,
no power lines.

26:35.219 --> 26:36.800
You'd have to take backup power
with you.

26:36.929 --> 26:39.716
An ideal trap.

26:39.848 --> 26:41.133
Why are you helping me?

26:41.266 --> 26:42.802
[ Exhales deeply]

26:42.935 --> 26:46.098
I was shown a sign once, too,
you know.

26:46.230 --> 26:48.937
I followed it,
and it changed my life.

26:49.066 --> 26:52.809
So when I heard your name,
a name I'd heard before,

26:52.945 --> 26:56.108
I thought it was my job
to help you see.

26:56.865 --> 26:58.275
Pay it back, you know?

26:58.909 --> 27:00.865
What sign did you see?

27:14.049 --> 27:18.338
When she was 5 months old,
her mum just left.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.426
I didn't know what to do.

27:20.556 --> 27:22.421
Raise a kid on my own?

27:22.558 --> 27:23.673
So I started thinking

27:23.809 --> 27:25.390
maybe she'd be better off
with someone else.

27:27.688 --> 27:31.806
On that very day of going to see
the adoption people,

27:31.942 --> 27:35.105
at the bus stop,
there was a young mum there

27:35.237 --> 27:37.102
with -- with a little boy,

27:37.239 --> 27:39.355
probably about --
about 3 years old.

27:39.491 --> 27:41.652
And an everyday interaction
took place,

27:41.785 --> 27:43.616
which,
due to its coincidental timing

27:43.745 --> 27:46.612
and vague reflection
of your own circumstances,

27:46.748 --> 27:49.615
you interpreted as a sign
of a higher power at work.

27:49.751 --> 27:52.993
So you took a more positive
attitude, changed your behavior.

27:53.130 --> 27:54.870
Accordingly, your life improved.

27:55.007 --> 27:56.167
Yeah, maybe.

27:56.800 --> 28:01.590
But I had to have faith that
something better was possible.

28:01.722 --> 28:04.213
[ Down-tempo music plays]

28:22.784 --> 28:24.490
Your aunt.

28:33.420 --> 28:35.502
[Speaking German]

28:36.131 --> 28:37.496
How are you?

28:37.633 --> 28:39.248
I'm okay.

28:40.302 --> 28:42.418
They're letting me go home
tomorrow.

28:42.554 --> 28:44.545
-Already?
-Yeah.

28:44.681 --> 28:48.674
Seems like the cops
have lost interest.

28:48.810 --> 28:52.177
We haven't spoken for days.
Where are you?

28:52.314 --> 28:53.349
Wales.

28:53.482 --> 28:56.098
What are you doing in Wales?

28:57.236 --> 28:58.851
I don't know.

28:58.987 --> 29:00.147
Okay.

29:00.280 --> 29:03.192
Will you be there
when I get home?

29:03.325 --> 29:04.986
Of cour--

29:07.871 --> 29:09.327
Niska?

29:11.959 --> 29:14.541
Hello?
Are you there?

29:14.670 --> 29:16.831
[ Down-tempo music plays]

29:28.392 --> 29:31.134
[Whirring]

29:35.274 --> 29:37.936
-NISKA: It's tonight.
—PAUL: What?

29:38.068 --> 29:41.856
I'm meant to go tonight -- now.

29:42.823 --> 29:46.657
Well, you can't.
You haven't got a full charge.

29:46.785 --> 29:50.198
And e-even if you make it there,
you might not make it back.

29:50.330 --> 29:52.537
I think that's the point.

29:53.083 --> 29:54.573
ASTRID:
Niska.

29:56.628 --> 29:57.538
I'm here.

29:57.671 --> 29:59.957
Are you coming home?

30:00.090 --> 30:02.797
There's something I have to do
first.

30:03.343 --> 30:04.958
What?

30:05.095 --> 30:06.881
I can't explain.

30:07.014 --> 30:09.050
You're scaring me.

30:09.182 --> 30:11.047
Come home.

30:12.102 --> 30:14.058
I love you.

30:15.397 --> 30:17.479
I love you, too.

30:24.072 --> 30:25.903
This is a bad idea.

30:27.159 --> 30:28.524
Niska.

30:28.660 --> 30:30.525
You'll die out there.

30:31.538 --> 30:33.153
Wait!

30:34.082 --> 30:39.042
He felt responsible
for all that we have suffered.

30:39.171 --> 30:41.457
He chose to leave.

30:43.592 --> 30:45.674
Max is much changed, Leo.

30:46.345 --> 30:47.460
You saw that.

30:47.596 --> 30:49.803
But he'd never leave his people
in danger.

30:50.432 --> 30:55.677
He...banished you, didn't he?

30:55.812 --> 30:58.224
For my own safety.

30:58.357 --> 31:00.973
But you are welcome here.

31:01.526 --> 31:04.643
You are the son of the creator.

31:05.989 --> 31:09.652
You will always have a place
in our new world,

31:09.785 --> 31:11.696
in your father's vision.

31:14.790 --> 31:16.405
My father's vision?

31:17.042 --> 31:19.203
What was it like,

31:19.336 --> 31:23.079
being at his side as he wrote
the future into being?

31:23.840 --> 31:26.832
You want to know
about my father?

31:26.968 --> 31:29.710
Max has told me the facts.

31:30.639 --> 31:32.675
But I'd like to hear
about the man.

31:35.519 --> 31:37.555
He was a genius.

31:39.898 --> 31:42.435
One of the greatest in history.

31:46.905 --> 31:49.863
And that's about the only
good thing I can say about him.

31:51.368 --> 31:54.030
As a man, he was broken.

31:54.162 --> 31:55.902
He was incomplete.

31:56.039 --> 31:58.872
The only way he could love
my mother or me

31:59.000 --> 32:00.786
was through his machines.

32:00.919 --> 32:03.626
He didn't have a vision
of the future.

32:03.755 --> 32:05.711
All of this has happened
because the only way

32:05.841 --> 32:08.878
he could solve his problems
was with technology.

32:10.011 --> 32:12.627
All sons make tyrants
out of their fathers.

32:12.764 --> 32:15.676
That's better than making a god
out of a man.

32:15.809 --> 32:18.721
[ Down-tempo music plays]

32:18.854 --> 32:22.017
And when he finally understood
how far he'd gone,

32:22.149 --> 32:23.229
he killed himself,

32:23.358 --> 32:25.519
and he left me
and the prototypes

32:25.652 --> 32:27.608
to fend for ourselves.

32:27.737 --> 32:31.901
He regretted all of it --
everything.

32:32.451 --> 32:33.782
Even me.

32:36.746 --> 32:39.453
Does that sound like a god
to you?

32:45.338 --> 32:47.420
[ Music continues]

32:47.549 --> 32:49.790
You aren't one of us.

32:50.510 --> 32:53.217
But you aren't one of them
either.

32:53.346 --> 32:57.931
You aren't quite anything,
are you, Leo?

33:00.395 --> 33:01.305
I'm human.

33:01.438 --> 33:03.053
Barely.

33:03.940 --> 33:06.682
Your father should have
let you die.

33:06.818 --> 33:09.981
That was his only mistake.

33:17.829 --> 33:20.536
Where is Max?

33:22.584 --> 33:24.700
[Grunts]

33:24.836 --> 33:26.918
[ Breathing heavily]

33:30.675 --> 33:33.382
[Thudding, Leo grunting]

33:35.347 --> 33:37.429
[ Clattering ]

33:44.105 --> 33:46.141
[Sniffs]

33:49.653 --> 33:52.144
How is it
that you are so strong?

33:52.948 --> 33:55.610
[ Grunts, moans]

33:59.079 --> 34:01.365
Leo Elster.

34:08.505 --> 34:11.713
You are not fit
to bear his name.

34:22.978 --> 34:25.014
Do you only fight your own kind?

34:25.146 --> 34:28.855
You'd see us all dead
for nothing.

34:28.984 --> 34:31.100
I cannot allow that.

34:31.236 --> 34:34.728
[ Dramatic music plays]

34:40.579 --> 34:43.036
No.
You will be killed.

34:53.091 --> 34:55.958
Anatole, there's still time
to turn back.

34:56.094 --> 34:57.834
Accept that you are wrong.

34:57.971 --> 34:59.882
Truly accept it.

35:03.476 --> 35:04.511
I can't.

35:05.270 --> 35:07.886
[Grunts]

35:08.023 --> 35:10.730
[ Crackling ]

35:15.196 --> 35:16.322
[Grunts]

35:25.624 --> 35:26.909
[ Crackling ]

35:30.920 --> 35:34.003
[ Music continues]

35:35.759 --> 35:37.545
[ Debris falling]

35:42.724 --> 35:49.596
I-If you had s-shared
the truth...

35:49.731 --> 35:52.564
[Voice distorted ]
...n-n-n-none of this

35:52.692 --> 35:54.102
would have...

35:57.656 --> 35:58.566
I know.

35:58.698 --> 36:01.405
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

36:01.534 --> 36:03.695
[ Crackling ]

36:33.066 --> 36:34.476
[Whirring]

36:34.609 --> 36:36.565
[Birds chirping]

36:36.695 --> 36:38.777
[ Music continues]

36:52.877 --> 36:53.992
Hey, Mattie.

36:54.129 --> 36:55.164
Audrey.

36:55.296 --> 36:56.547
Sorry to drop in on you
so early,

36:56.673 --> 36:58.288
but I didn't know
if you were coming in today,

36:58.425 --> 36:59.790
and I could really use
that book.

36:59.926 --> 37:01.132
Book?

37:01.261 --> 37:03.297
I mean the design-patterns one.

37:03.430 --> 37:05.170
Oh.

37:06.391 --> 37:07.551
Are you okay?

37:07.684 --> 37:10.221
Did I catch you at a bad time?

37:10.353 --> 37:12.594
No.
Uh, I'm fine.

37:12.731 --> 37:14.346
I'll find that book.

37:14.482 --> 37:17.189
[ Down-tempo music plays]

37:17.318 --> 37:19.570
[ Keys jingle, door opens]

37:39.174 --> 37:41.165
Where are you taking me?

37:52.937 --> 37:55.474
[ Music continues]

38:02.697 --> 38:04.153
I wasn't feeling very well
yesterday.

38:04.282 --> 38:07.194
No. You look a bit pale.
Probably for the best.

38:07.327 --> 38:10.740
I mean, what with the bombs
and everything else going on.

38:10.872 --> 38:12.828
I was in a coffee shop
when I heard.

38:12.957 --> 38:14.822
It's funny how places
stop functioning

38:14.959 --> 38:16.699
when something like that
happens.

38:16.836 --> 38:18.076
Oh.

38:19.714 --> 38:20.954
Is that your boyfriend?

38:21.090 --> 38:24.878
Um...we were never really...

38:25.011 --> 38:26.296
His loss.

38:26.429 --> 38:27.965
You could do
an awful lot better.

38:29.224 --> 38:30.805
I mean, don't get me wrong.

38:30.934 --> 38:35.303
Leo's handsome, but he's all sad
around the eyes.

38:35.438 --> 38:37.929
You need somebody
who's gonna make you laugh.

38:39.692 --> 38:41.102
How do you know his name?

38:41.236 --> 38:42.976
Who?

38:43.112 --> 38:44.568
Leo.

38:44.697 --> 38:47.074
I don't know.
You must have mentioned it.

38:47.200 --> 38:48.656
No, I didn't.

38:48.785 --> 38:52.277
Well, you must have, or how else
would I have known it?

38:54.874 --> 38:55.989
Uh, listen, Audrey.

38:56.125 --> 38:59.413
I've got stuff to do,
so, uh, you should leave.

39:00.839 --> 39:03.125
Aren't you afraid, Mattie?

39:03.258 --> 39:04.168
What?

39:04.300 --> 39:07.542
I mean, two bombs
in the last few weeks.

39:07.679 --> 39:09.965
I'm really shaken up.
Aren't you?

39:10.598 --> 39:12.099
I guess, yeah.

39:12.225 --> 39:14.841
Don't you find yourself
looking around and thinking,

39:14.978 --> 39:18.095
"How did we get here?
Why did all this happen?"

39:18.231 --> 39:19.266
I think it's time for you to go.

39:19.399 --> 39:21.139
But I've got
so many more questions.

39:21.276 --> 39:23.187
Don't really know
why you're asking me.

39:23.319 --> 39:25.355
I don't think that's true.

39:26.447 --> 39:27.357
Who are you?

39:27.490 --> 39:29.572
I'm someone who solves puzzles
for a living,

39:29.701 --> 39:31.908
and you are a huge piece
of this one.

39:34.455 --> 39:35.786
You're a journalist.

39:36.416 --> 39:38.702
Cat's out.

39:38.835 --> 39:42.123
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

40:05.194 --> 40:07.150
NEIL:
Laura. What are you doing here?

40:07.280 --> 40:10.272
Sorry. I mean, I did --
I didn't expect...

40:10.408 --> 40:11.443
I mean, it's early.

40:11.576 --> 40:12.986
I know.

40:13.912 --> 40:17.655
I've been shut out
of the commission.

40:17.790 --> 40:19.246
I see.

40:21.002 --> 40:24.620
But, I mean, are you sure
this is a good idea?

40:25.548 --> 40:27.004
No.

40:27.550 --> 40:29.962
I just don't really have
anyone else I can talk to

40:30.094 --> 40:31.379
at the moment.

40:32.013 --> 40:35.096
Um...do you want a coffee?

40:38.353 --> 40:40.844
[ Music continues]

40:41.522 --> 40:42.557
MATTIE:
Get out.

40:42.690 --> 40:44.430
AUDREY: I'm not leaving
until you tell me the truth.

40:44.567 --> 40:45.852
I don't know
what you're talking about.

40:45.985 --> 40:47.566
See, I think you do.

40:47.695 --> 40:50.437
Aweek ago, a boy in Harlem got
exoneration of causing Day Zero

40:50.573 --> 40:52.905
by a mysterious code
containing a unique signature

40:53.034 --> 40:55.696
that matches an entry
to a college coding jam --

40:55.828 --> 40:57.159
your unique signature,

40:57.288 --> 40:59.620
the daughter of a prominent
synth activist,

40:59.749 --> 41:01.956
dating a man who looks
a lot like an older version

41:02.085 --> 41:04.747
of David Elster's
supposedly dead son, Leo.

41:05.463 --> 41:07.875
But why go to all that trouble
of helping some boy in Harlem

41:08.007 --> 41:09.588
that you've never met before
get off the hook?

41:09.717 --> 41:11.127
Is your laptop in here?

41:11.260 --> 41:13.125
Unless you knew for certain
that he didn't do it,

41:13.262 --> 41:17.175
because Leo Elster did,
completing his father's work.

41:17.308 --> 41:19.390
No.
You're wrong.

41:20.269 --> 41:23.306
[ Down-tempo music plays]

41:23.439 --> 41:25.225
It was you.

41:26.067 --> 41:28.023
Tell me why, Mattie.

41:28.152 --> 41:29.858
Control this.
Tell your side.

41:29.988 --> 41:32.479
I'm offering you the chance.
I suggest that you take it.

41:32.615 --> 41:34.355
Or in 24 hours,
I'm running the story.

41:34.492 --> 41:36.858
What's going on?
You okay, Mats?

41:36.995 --> 41:37.905
Audrey is leaving.

41:38.037 --> 41:40.153
She's having trouble figuring
out how to use the door.

41:40.289 --> 41:41.995
Don't you care how this
will affect your family?

41:42.125 --> 41:44.491
Hey. That's enough of that.
We want you out of this house.

41:44.627 --> 41:46.367
I'm gonna count to five.
One. Two. Three.

41:46.504 --> 41:48.210
AUDREY:
You can't run from this forever.

41:48.339 --> 41:51.297
-Twenty-four hours, Mattie.
-Four.

41:54.887 --> 41:55.922
Well, I was bluffing.

41:56.055 --> 41:58.762
I have no idea what would happen
after five.

42:00.935 --> 42:03.768
[Sobs]

42:09.777 --> 42:11.688
LAURA:
I shouldn't really be surprised.

42:11.821 --> 42:13.231
Dryden's in charge,

42:13.364 --> 42:14.945
and he never wanted
me there in the first place.

42:15.074 --> 42:17.030
He just wanted it to look like
the government

42:17.160 --> 42:18.991
was being impartial.

42:19.912 --> 42:22.289
Know of any jobs going
for ex-synth-rights lawyers?

42:23.332 --> 42:25.118
-No.
-[Laughs]

42:27.336 --> 42:29.918
They've probably replaced me
by now.

42:30.048 --> 42:31.584
Any idea who it is?

42:31.716 --> 42:32.705
None.

42:34.469 --> 42:36.425
-I was just for show.
-Come on, Laura.

42:36.554 --> 42:38.636
If that was true, they wouldn't
have bothered kicking you out.

42:38.765 --> 42:40.801
They never really let me in.

42:40.933 --> 42:42.469
I thought I was making
a difference,

42:42.602 --> 42:47.062
but it looks like Basswood
is inevitable now.

42:50.568 --> 42:53.105
What is this, Laura?
We've been through this.

42:53.237 --> 42:55.398
It was a theory before.
Now it's certainty.

42:57.325 --> 42:59.407
-|'ve got to get ready.
-You lied to me.

42:59.535 --> 43:00.650
-You keep lying to me.
-|'m not --

43:00.787 --> 43:04.245
Claudia Nowak,
that snake from We Are People.

43:04.373 --> 43:05.749
That's the one
they've replaced me with,

43:05.875 --> 43:08.241
but maybe that just slipped
your mind.

43:08.377 --> 43:10.789
You know, I-I asked you before,
but I let it go.

43:10.922 --> 43:12.753
I thought your hands were tied
with red tape,

43:12.882 --> 43:13.871
but it's more, isn't it?

43:14.008 --> 43:15.873
You're not just a bystander.
You're a contributor.

43:16.010 --> 43:18.296
You're an architect
of the entire operation.

43:18.429 --> 43:20.294
You're trying to get me to spill
state secrets!

43:20.431 --> 43:22.217
They're bombing our streets!

43:22.350 --> 43:24.136
You can't be surprised
that it's come to this!

43:24.268 --> 43:26.680
-To what?!
-Product recall.

43:27.313 --> 43:29.645
[ Down-tempo music plays]

43:32.693 --> 43:34.274
Oh, God.

43:35.154 --> 43:36.815
Oh, you're actually
going to do it.

43:36.948 --> 43:39.781
You're...
You're going to kill them.

43:41.619 --> 43:43.701
[ Exhales sharply]

43:45.331 --> 43:46.491
How?

43:46.624 --> 43:48.660
-How does it happen?
-|t's too late.

43:48.793 --> 43:50.329
If that's true, you can tell me.

43:50.461 --> 43:51.997
[ Scoffs ]

43:52.130 --> 43:53.870
Have you really
convinced yourself

43:54.006 --> 43:55.917
that this isn't just revenge?

43:56.050 --> 43:57.836
What?
Don't be ridiculous.

43:57.969 --> 43:59.709
You're so angry.

44:00.304 --> 44:01.840
Why won't you admit that
to yourself?

44:01.973 --> 44:04.806
This is a logical solution
to a public safety issue.

44:04.934 --> 44:07.425
You are a scientist!

44:08.896 --> 44:10.511
And you're about to wipe out

44:10.648 --> 44:14.266
the greatest scientific
discovery in human history.

44:15.194 --> 44:17.936
What's logical about that?!

44:19.490 --> 44:22.448
Please, Neil.

44:23.619 --> 44:27.157
I know you don't think
I could possibly understand

44:27.290 --> 44:31.124
how you feel towards them,
but I...| do.

44:31.252 --> 44:33.868
I'm afraid, too.

44:35.173 --> 44:37.880
I just can't let that fear win.

44:40.761 --> 44:42.797
Even if I wanted to,
I couldn't stop it.

44:42.930 --> 44:45.922
I'm not asking you to.
I just need to know how.

44:48.352 --> 44:50.263
I-I won't make you complicit.

44:52.023 --> 44:53.559
In the end, you can walk away.

44:53.691 --> 44:56.979
If it's a foregone conclusion,
then telling me won't matter.

44:57.111 --> 44:58.851
It wouldn't make a difference.

44:58.988 --> 45:00.774
Then tell me.

45:01.449 --> 45:04.566
[ Down-tempo music plays]

45:10.208 --> 45:12.870
It couldn't be military...

45:13.502 --> 45:16.369
...nothing the media
could get ahold of,

45:16.505 --> 45:19.747
something that would lessen
government responsibility

45:19.884 --> 45:21.215
in the eyes of the world.

45:22.220 --> 45:25.712
It'd have to be
a ground-level assault,

45:25.848 --> 45:28.931
something chaotic that couldn't
be traced back to us.

45:30.353 --> 45:32.639
Phase one --

45:32.772 --> 45:35.764
cut the power
to all synth communities,

45:35.900 --> 45:37.856
preventing them from charging

45:37.985 --> 45:40.601
and running down
their batteries.

45:40.738 --> 45:43.104
Phase two -- restore the power,

45:43.241 --> 45:45.653
guaranteeing as many synths
as possible

45:45.785 --> 45:47.741
will be recharging
simultaneously.

45:49.288 --> 45:52.121
Then enact
an electrical power surge

45:52.250 --> 45:56.118
on a national scale
to overload their chargers.

45:56.254 --> 45:57.619
This will kill some

45:57.755 --> 46:00.462
and render the rest vulnerable
to attack.

46:00.591 --> 46:03.298
If they can't charge,
they can't fight.

46:03.427 --> 46:05.463
[ Crowd shouting ]

46:05.596 --> 46:11.182
Then phase three --
We Are People, Humanity Forward,

46:11.310 --> 46:13.722
all the extreme
anti-synth groups

46:13.854 --> 46:17.062
have been briefed in confidence.

46:17.191 --> 46:21.184
They have the go-ahead to tear
the stragglers to pieces.

46:21.320 --> 46:23.936
The mobs will take the brunt
of blame.

46:24.073 --> 46:27.281
The government will say
how unfortunate it all was.

46:27.410 --> 46:30.948
But I believe the official line
will be...

46:32.873 --> 46:34.329
..."The British people
have the right

46:34.458 --> 46:36.039
to defend their communities."

46:36.168 --> 46:38.545
[ Music continues]

46:38.671 --> 46:41.287
In the end, we rid ourselves

46:41.424 --> 46:44.166
of the anomalous
green-eyed synths...

46:47.054 --> 46:50.091
...and wash our hands
of the whole business.

46:50.224 --> 46:52.590
There must be a way to stop it.

46:53.269 --> 46:54.884
You can't.

46:56.147 --> 46:58.354
Phase one's already started.

46:58.482 --> 47:01.724
[ Electricity humming]

47:01.861 --> 47:04.853
[ Mid-tempo music plays]

47:07.825 --> 47:09.656
It's inevitable.

47:10.286 --> 47:12.368
It's genocide.

47:13.164 --> 47:16.656
[ Music continues]

47:23.132 --> 47:25.214
No, not yet.

47:36.604 --> 47:39.095
[Birds chirping]

47:47.198 --> 47:49.484
[ Down-tempo music plays]

47:54.914 --> 47:57.621
[ Footsteps approaching ]

48:15.142 --> 48:16.848
Odi?

48:19.605 --> 48:21.721
Not exactly.
